---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Kapil Reddy" />
		<style>
			main {
				width: 90%;
				max-width: 900px;
				margin: 3em auto;
				padding: 2em 1em;
			}

			article {
				background: var(--card-bg);
				border: 4px solid var(--border);
				box-shadow: var(--box-shadow-light);
				padding: 3rem;
				transition: var(--transition);
				position: relative;
			}

			body.dark-mode article {
				box-shadow: var(--box-shadow-dark);
			}

			article::before {
				content: "◐";
				position: absolute;
				top: -15px;
				right: 2rem;
				font-size: 3rem;
				color: var(--primary);
			}

			h1 {
				font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
				color: var(--border);
				text-align: center;
				padding: 1rem 2rem;
				background: var(--primary);
				border: 3px solid var(--border);
				box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px 0px var(--border);
				font-family: var(--font-heading);
				font-weight: 900;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				letter-spacing: -1px;
				display: inline-block;
				width: 100%;
			}

			h3 {
				font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem);
				margin: 2.5rem 0 1.5rem;
				color: var(--text-primary);
				border-left: 6px solid var(--accent-1);
				padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
				background: var(--card-bg);
				border: 3px solid var(--border);
				border-left-width: 6px;
				box-shadow: 4px 4px 0px 0px var(--border);
				font-family: var(--font-heading);
				font-weight: 900;
				text-transform: uppercase;
				letter-spacing: 0.5px;
			}

			h3::before {
				content: "▶";
				margin-right: 0.5rem;
				color: var(--accent-1);
			}

			p {
				margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
				line-height: 1.8;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
			}

			strong {
				color: var(--accent-1);
				font-weight: 900;
				background: var(--primary);
				padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
				border: 2px solid var(--border);
				font-family: var(--font-heading);
				text-transform: uppercase;
				letter-spacing: 0.5px;
				font-size: 0.95em;
			}

			img {
				display: block;
				margin: 2rem auto;
				max-width: 300px;
				border: 4px solid var(--border);
				border-radius: 0px;
				box-shadow: 8px 8px 0px 0px var(--border);
				transition: var(--transition);
				transform: rotate(-2deg);
			}

			img:hover {
				transform: translate(-2px, -2px) rotate(2deg);
				box-shadow: 10px 10px 0px 0px var(--border);
			}

			ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
				margin: 1.5rem 0;
			}

		ul li {
			padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem;
			margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
			background: transparent;
			border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
			transition: var(--transition);
		}

		ul li:hover {
			background: var(--card-bg);
			border-left-color: var(--accent-1);
			padding-left: 1.5rem;
		}

		ul li a {
			color: var(--text-primary);
			text-decoration: none;
			font-weight: 700;
			transition: var(--transition);
		}

		ul li a:hover {
			color: var(--accent-1);
			text-decoration: underline;
			text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
		}

			@media (max-width: 768px) {
				article {
					padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
				}

				h1 {
					font-size: 2rem;
					padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
				}

				img {
					max-width: 100%;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article>
				<h1>About</h1>
				
				<p>I am Kapil Reddy. I am a builder and storyteller.</p>

				<p>I started my journey as a Javascripter. Hacked a bunch of POCs some of which survived as production code. At Helpshift, I also built a core-infra team from 2 engineers to 20 engineers. I have built planet scale (2 Bn devices) distributed systems in Clojure and Python.</p>

				<p><strong>Fractional leadership: Tech</strong></p>

				<p>The hacker years, I started my journey as a JS + PHP developer. Later, I joined Infinitelybeta where I learnt to build things with Clojure and Python. Infinitelybeta a product studio narrowed down on building Helphshift. I continued building quick POCs like a co-browsing experience to Android SDKs. Some of them survived to be part of the product even to this day.</p>

				<p>The engineering years, The POCs I built worked for a while Helpshift hit PMF. We were on a rocketship. But some of the POCs were not built for this.</p>

				<img src="/images/profile.jpeg" alt="Kapil Reddy" />

				<p><strong>What I do now. Unravel.</strong></p>

				<h3>Presentations</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PLOtpbdqDxY" target="_blank">Belaying growth</a></li>
					<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FGxjqxXucsM&t=6s" target="_blank">Clojure North - Concurrency workshop</a></li>
					<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sxxcDNbvCNE" target="_blank">Build scalable and reliable services in Clojure - Clojure North</a></li>
				</ul>

				<h3>What I write about</h3>
				<ul>
					<li>Leadership for tech and craft based work</li>
					<li>War stories and lessons from building things at scale</li>
					<li>Musings about future of tech</li>
					<li>Journals of building things</li>
					<li>Visual storytelling</li>
				</ul>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
